  "text": "Recent studies also attribute the resection of unprotected nascent DNA at stalled forks to EXO1 and CTiP. Depletion of either of these nucleases rescues nascent strand degradation in BRCA2deficient cells [CITATION_1] . Similarly, knockdown of EXO1 rescues reversed fork levels that are decreased in BRCA1/2deficient cells treated with replication stress-inducing drugs [CITATION_2] . These data put forth a working model of resection at unprotected replication forks in the BRCA2-deficient setting that looks remarkably similar to the genetic requirements for resection at DSBs. In the absence of BRCA2, resection may be initiated by CTiP and MRE11 followed by more extensive processing by EXO1.",
